(((
**Why it fits:** Innosuisse fits applied collaboration with a concrete implementation partner, but it is only one viable route among several and should be chosen only if it matches the partner, scope, and timing.
)))

=== Alternative / Complementary Paths ===

|=Route|=Best For|=Notes
|**ETH — Prof. Elliott Ash**|Deep NLP research on claim detection, evidence retrieval, debate frameworks|AFaCTA (ACL 2024), e-FEVER, BallotBot (RAG). Strong publication record but no confirmed Innosuisse history. Could be a direct partner, academic advisor, or co-PI depending on project structure.
|**UZH — Prof. Markus Leippold**|Climate-specific fact-checking, domain extension|Climinator (96% accuracy, debate architecture). Primarily climate-focused; general-domain extension would be novel for this group.
|**SNSF / Hasler Foundation**|Fundamental research questions|Hasler "Responsible AI" programme previously funded "Scientific Claim Verification" (Sachan + Leippold + Ash). Suitable for longer-term, more theoretical work.
|**BRIDGE Proof of Concept**|Academic-led commercialization|Initiated from the research partner side. Up to CHF 130K/year. Deadlines 2026: March 2, June 1, September 1, December 1.
|**Student projects**|Low-cost exploration|Bachelor/Master theses on specific pipeline components. This can be a practical entry point for testing focused ideas before committing to a larger collaboration.

(% class="box infomessage" style="background-color:#eef3f8;border-color:#9db4cb;" %)
(((
**Released operation needs separate financing:** Research funding can support development, evaluation, and transfer work, but long-term operation of a public-facing service needs its own sustainability model. Plausible options include institutional partnerships, public-interest foundation grants, professional service / API contracts, community support, and infrastructure sponsors such as cloud or LLM-credit programmes.
)))

