== Goals for First Public Release (V1.0) ==

The pipeline works end-to-end today. To move from working prototype to a public service people can rely on, five engineering goals must be met:

|=Goal|=Current State|=V1.0 Target
|**Scalability**|Single host, 3 concurrent jobs|Horizontal scaling, queue-based dispatch
|**Performance**|~3-5 min per analysis|< 90 seconds via caching and parallel execution
|**Stability**|Operational but manual recovery|Auto-recovery, health monitoring, graceful degradation
|**Repeatability**|Verdicts can vary across runs (LLM stochasticity, live evidence)|Stability within defined tolerance bands; evidence caching
|**Cost Reduction**|~$0.15-0.25 per analysis|< $0.05 via caching, smaller models, evidence reuse

(% class="box successmessage" style="background-color:#e5f4bf;border-color:#7fb36a;" %)
(((
**Research angle:** These V1.0 goals create measurable constraints for the "resource-efficient fact verification" framing. Speed and cost reduction motivate small-model substitution and low-latency systems work. Repeatability motivates stability and reproducibility work. Precision motivates evidence sufficiency studies. The engineering roadmap is therefore a useful experimental baseline, not a substitute for formal research design.
)))

