== Current Status ==

=== What Works ===

|=Area|=Status|=Details
|**ClaimAssessmentBoundary (CB) Pipeline (all 5 stages)**|Working in Alpha|Extract Claims, Research, Cluster Boundaries, Verdict, Aggregate — operational end-to-end, with known repeatability and product-maturity gaps documented below
|**Multi-Provider LLM Debate**|Working|Anthropic advocate + OpenAI challenger, self-consistency, reconciler, validator
|**Quality Gates (Gate 1 + Gate 4)**|Working|Claim validation and confidence tiering with UI panel
|**UCM Configuration**|Working|All analysis parameters tunable at runtime via Admin UI, hot-reloadable, with per-job config snapshots for reproducibility
|**Source Reliability v2**|Working|LLM-powered assessment, cache isolation, and evidence weighting are active; the optional Stage 4.5 calibration path exists but remains disabled by default pending validation
|**Multi-Provider Search**|Working|7 providers integrated (web search, Wikipedia, Semantic Scholar, Google Fact Check); automatic fallback
|**LLM Model Tiering**|Working|Budget models for extraction, standard models for verdicts, cross-provider challenger for debate diversity
|**Multilingual Analysis**|Working|DE, EN, FR, PT tested; no English-only logic in active pipeline code
|**Input Neutrality**|Working|"Was X fair?" vs "X was fair" within ±4% tolerance
|**HTML Report Generation**|Working|Structured reports with evidence citations, per-boundary findings

=== What's Open ===

|=Area|=Status|=What's Needed
|**User Authentication**|Not started|Currently invite-code only; needs proper user accounts, OAuth, RBAC
|**Performance**|Needs improvement|~3-5 min per claim; target < 90 seconds via caching and parallel execution
|**Repeatability**|Partially addressed|Self-consistency gating implemented; evidence caching and tolerance bands needed
|**Observability**|Partial|Pipeline metrics collection working; production dashboards and alerting not yet set up
|**Horizontal Scaling**|Not started|Single-host only; needs queue-based dispatch for concurrent users
|**Claim Caching**|Partial|Search-level caching working; full evidence reuse across analyses planned (30-50% cost savings expected)

=== Known Problems & Challenges ===

(% class="box warningmessage" %)
(((
**Transparency note:** These are real, active challenges — not theoretical risks. Being open about them is part of FactHarbor's commitment to honesty.
)))

**Report Stability** — the most significant quality challenge:

Running the same claim twice can produce meaningfully different verdicts. Three compounding factors:

|=Factor|=Cause|=Impact|=Mitigation Status
|**LLM Stochasticity**|Even at temperature 0, LLM outputs are not fully deterministic|Verdict percentages can shift 5-15pp between runs|Self-consistency check (Step 2) measures stability; high spread reduces confidence
|**Live Web Evidence**|Evidence changes daily — sources go offline, new articles appear, search rankings shift|Different evidence base → different conclusions|Partially mitigated; evidence caching planned but not built
|**Claim Decomposition Variance**|The same input text can be decomposed into different AtomicClaims across runs|Different claims → different research → different verdicts|Gate 1 tightening (Phase B) planned; two-pass extraction reduces but doesn't eliminate variance

(% class="box successmessage" style="background-color:#e5f4bf;border-color:#7fb36a;" %)
(((
**Research opportunity:** Report stability is a measurable problem. Defining formal stability metrics, establishing tolerance bands, and designing reproducibility protocols for LLM-based fact-checking systems.
)))

**Other active challenges:**

|=Problem|=Details
|**Broad claim over-decomposition**|Rhetorical claims sometimes decomposed too aggressively — weak sub-claims survive Gate 1 and dilute analysis quality
|**Source reliability evaluation quality**|LLM-based source evaluation is functional but not yet benchmarked against human expert assessments
|**Cost per analysis**|~$0.15-0.25 is acceptable for Alpha but too high for a free public service at scale

