=== Source Reliability as a Standalone Service ===

The Source Reliability (SR) module — which evaluates domain credibility using multi-provider LLM assessment — is designed for **extraction as an independent service**. It already has its own database, cache isolation, and UCM configuration. As a standalone API, it could serve:

* **Other fact-checking platforms** — any system that needs domain credibility scores
* **Newsrooms** — evaluate source trustworthiness before citing
* **Researchers** — systematic, reproducible media source assessment at scale
* **Browser extensions** — real-time credibility indicators while browsing

=== Accessibility & Internationalization ===

|=Feature|=Target|=Why
|**WCAG 2.1 AA Compliance**|Beta+|Screen readers, keyboard navigation, high-contrast modes
|**Multilingual UI (10+ languages)**|V1.0+|Interface beyond English — matching the multilingual analysis capability
|**RTL Language Support**|V1.5+|Arabic, Hebrew, and other right-to-left languages

