=== Pipeline Stages and Model Tiering ===

|=Stage|=Name|=What Happens|=Model Tier
|1|**Extract Claims**|Pass 1 scan, preliminary web grounding, Pass 2 grounded extraction, centrality filter, Gate 1 validation|Budget + Web Search
|2|**Research**|Iterative query generation, web search, relevance screening, source fetch, evidence extraction, and evidence filtering|Budget + Web Search
|3|**Cluster Boundaries**|Collect scopes, optionally normalize equivalent scopes, then cluster into ClaimAssessmentBoundaries|Budget + Standard
|4|**Verdict**|5-step adversarial LLM debate per claim (see below)|Sonnet (standard)
|4.5|//**SR Calibration**// (optional)|An optional calibration path exists for LLM-backed source portfolio adjustment, but it remains disabled by default pending validation.|Budget
|5|**Aggregate**|Weighted aggregation with triangulation, narrative generation|Sonnet (standard)

=== LLM Call Topology ===

|=Pipeline Part|=Typical Call Pattern
|**Stage 1: Claim extraction**|Pass 1 scan + Pass 2 evidence-grounded extraction + Gate 1 validation (batched budget-tier calls)
|**Stage 2: Research**|Repeated budget-tier calls for query generation, relevance classification, and evidence extraction across search rounds
|**Stage 3: Boundary clustering**|Scope normalization plus clustering calls to form ClaimAssessmentBoundaries
|**Stage 4: Verdict debate**|1 advocate + 2 self-consistency re-runs + 1 challenger + 1 reconciler + 2 lightweight validator checks
|**Stage 5: Final report**|Aggregation / narrative generation call for the published result

=== Loop and Retry Topology ===

The production pipeline contains multiple control-flow loops and retries beyond the simplified sufficiency-check arrow shown above.

{{mermaid}}
flowchart TB
    subgraph S1["Stage 1: Claim Extraction Loops"]
        direction LR
        P1["Pass 1 scan"]:::llmCall
        PRE["Preliminary web grounding"]:::searchCall
        P2["Pass 2 grounded extraction"]:::llmCall
        P2R["Pass 2 retry / fallback\n(hardcoded retry limit)"]:::llmCall
        G1["Gate 1 validation"]:::llmCall
        ENOUGH{"Enough claims\npost-Gate 1?"}:::decision
        REP["Reprompt Pass 2 + Gate 1\n(UCM-configured attempts)"]:::llmCall

        P1 -->|"rough claims"| PRE -->|"preliminary evidence"| P2 -->|"candidate claims"| G1 -->|"validated claims"| ENOUGH
        P2 -.->|"soft refusal / schema issue"| P2R -->|"retry context"| P2
        ENOUGH -->|"No"| REP -->|"guidance + input"| P2
    end

    subgraph S2["Stage 2: Research Iteration Loops"]
        direction TB
        MAIN{"Continue main loop?\n(sufficiency, time,\nbudget, zero-yield)"}:::decision
        PICK["Pick least-researched claim"]:::neutral

        subgraph ITER["Per-iteration research"]
            direction LR
            QGEN["Generate queries"]:::llmCall
            SEARCH["Web search"]:::searchCall
            REL["Relevance screening"]:::llmCall
            FETCH["Fetch sources"]:::searchCall
            FRETRY["Fetch retry once\n(transient errors)"]:::searchCall
            EX["Extract evidence + scopes"]:::llmCall
            CHECK["Scope / derivative checks\n+ evidence filter"]:::neutral

            QGEN -->|"queries"| SEARCH -->|"search results"| REL -->|"relevant URLs"| FETCH -->|"fetched sources"| EX -->|"evidence items + scopes"| CHECK
            FETCH -.->|"timeout / network / 5xx"| FRETRY -->|"retried fetch"| FETCH
        end

        CONTRA{"Contradiction\niterations left?"}:::decision
        CONTRA_RUN["Contradiction iteration\n(pick least-contradicted claim)"]:::searchCall
        SKEW{"Evidence pool\nskewed?"}:::decision
        CONTRARIAN["Contrarian retrieval\n(for each claim)"]:::searchCall

        MAIN -->|"Yes"| PICK -->|"target claim"| QGEN
        CHECK -->|"updated evidence pool"| MAIN
        MAIN -->|"No"| CONTRA
        CONTRA -->|"Yes"| CONTRA_RUN -->|"contradicting evidence"| CONTRA
        CONTRA -->|"No"| SKEW
        SKEW -->|"Yes"| CONTRARIAN
    end

    subgraph S3["Stage 3: Boundary Clustering Loops"]
        direction LR
        NS{"Normalize scopes?"}:::decision
        NORM["LLM scope normalization"]:::llmCall
        CL["LLM clustering"]:::llmCall
        CAP{"Within max\nboundaries?"}:::decision
        MERGE["Merge closest boundaries"]:::neutral

        NS -->|"Yes: unique scopes"| NORM -->|"normalized scopes"| CL -->|"candidate boundaries"| CAP
        NS -->|"No: unique scopes"| CL
        CAP -->|"No"| MERGE -->|"merged boundaries"| CAP
    end

    subgraph S4["Stage 4: Verdict Loops"]
        direction TB
        ADV["Advocate"]:::llmCall

        subgraph PAR["Parallel branch"]
            direction LR
            SC["Self-consistency\n(run2 + run3)"]:::llmCall
            CH["Challenger"]:::llmCall
        end

        SCRETRY["Retry failed\nself-consistency run once"]:::llmCall
        REC["Reconciliation"]:::llmCall
        VAL["Grounding + direction\nvalidation"]:::llmCall
        VRETRY["Validation batch\nretry once"]:::llmCall
        REPAIR["Direction repair\n+ revalidate"]:::llmCall

        ADV -->|"advocate verdicts"| SC
        ADV -->|"advocate verdicts"| CH
        SC -.->|"run failure"| SCRETRY -->|"retried run"| SC
        SC -->|"consistency spread"| REC
        CH -->|"challenge document"| REC
        REC -->|"reconciled verdicts"| VAL
        VAL -.->|"batch failure"| VRETRY -->|"retried validation"| VAL
        VAL -.->|"direction issue\nand policy enabled"| REPAIR -->|"repaired verdict"| VAL
    end

    SRCAL45["Stage 4.5: SR Calibration\n(optional, disabled by default)"]:::llmCall
    FINAL["Stage 5: Aggregate + report\n(no control-flow loop)"]:::neutral

    ENOUGH -->|"Yes: AtomicClaims"| MAIN
    SKEW -->|"No: EvidenceItems"| NS
    CONTRARIAN -->|"expanded evidence pool"| NS
    CAP -->|"Yes: ClaimBoundaries + CoverageMatrix"| ADV
    VAL -->|"ClaimVerdicts"| SRCAL45
    SRCAL45 -->|"Calibrated verdicts"| FINAL

    style S1 fill:#e8f5e9,stroke:#2e7d32,color:#000
    style S2 fill:#fff9c4,stroke:#f57f17,color:#000
    style S3 fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#1565c0,color:#000
    style S4 fill:#f3e5f5,stroke:#7b1fa2,color:#000
    style PAR fill:#fafafa,stroke:#d9d9d9,color:#000,stroke-dasharray:5 3
    classDef llmCall fill:#f3e5f5,stroke:#7b1fa2,color:#4a148c,stroke-width:1.8px
    classDef searchCall fill:#fff3e0,stroke:#e65100,color:#bf360c,stroke-width:1.8px
    classDef neutral fill:#f3fbf4,stroke:#7cb889,color:#1f4d2a,stroke-width:1.5px
    classDef decision fill:#fffde7,stroke:#c0a800,color:#6d4c00,stroke-width:1.5px
{{/mermaid}}

----

== Structured AI Debate ==

Every claim goes through a **adversarial debate**. Different providers argue against each other. An objection only counts as "contested" if it cites specific counter-evidence — unsupported criticism is classified as "doubted" and cannot change a verdict.

{{mermaid}}
flowchart LR
    E[Evidence + Boundaries] --> S1

    subgraph INTERNAL["Internal Debate Pipeline"]
        direction LR
        S1[1. Advocate]
        S4[4. Reconciliation]
        S5[5. Validation]

        subgraph "Parallel Execution"
            S2[2. Self-Consistency x2]
            S3[3. Adversarial Challenge]
        end

        S1 --> S2
        S1 --> S3
        S2 --> S4
        S3 --> S4
    end

    S4 --> S5
    S5 --> O[Final Verdict]

    ANTH["Anthropic API Calls<br/>Advocate, Self-Consistency,<br/>Reconciler, Validator"]
    OPENAI["OpenAI API Call<br/>Challenger (GPT-4.1)"]

    S1 -.-> ANTH
    S2 -.-> ANTH
    S4 -.-> ANTH
    S5 -.-> ANTH
    S3 -.-> OPENAI

    style S1 fill:#e8f5e9,stroke:#2e7d32
    style S2 fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#1565c0
    style S3 fill:#fff3e0,stroke:#e65100
    style S4 fill:#f3e5f5,stroke:#7b1fa2
    style S5 fill:#fce4ec,stroke:#c2185b
    style INTERNAL fill:#f9fbff,stroke:#90a4ae,color:#000,stroke-width:1.5px
    style ANTH fill:#F3E5F5,stroke:#7B1FA2,color:#4A148C,stroke-width:2px
    style OPENAI fill:#F3E5F5,stroke:#7B1FA2,color:#4A148C,stroke-width:2px
{{/mermaid}}

=== Debate Roles ===

|=Step|=Role|=Function|=Provider
|1|**Advocate**|Build the strongest evidence-backed case for the most supported interpretation|Anthropic (Sonnet)
|2|**Self-Consistency**|Two parallel re-runs at elevated temperature — measures verdict stability|Anthropic (Sonnet)
|3|**Challenger**|Adversarial challenge from a //different provider// for model diversity|OpenAI (GPT-4.1)
|4|**Reconciler**|Final verdict integrating challenge insights and stability data|Anthropic (Sonnet)
|5|**Validator**|Grounding check + direction check (advisory, non-blocking)|Anthropic (Haiku)

(% class="box infomessage" %)
(((
**Cross-provider diversity:** Steps 2 and 3 run in parallel. Using different LLM providers for Advocate vs. Challenger prevents single-model echo-chamber bias — a known weakness in single-provider fact-checking systems.
)))

----

== Verdict Transparency ==

Verdicts are not binary. The system reports a **7-point scale** with confidence levels, so you know whether a claim is overwhelmingly supported, genuinely mixed, or contradicted — and how confident the system is.

{{mermaid}}
flowchart LR
    TRUE["TRUE\n86-100%"]
    MT["MOSTLY\nTRUE\n72-85%"]
    LT["LEANING\nTRUE\n58-71%"]
    MIXED["MIXED /\nUNVERIFIED\n43-57%"]
    LF["LEANING\nFALSE\n29-42%"]
    MF["MOSTLY\nFALSE\n15-28%"]
    FALSE["FALSE\n0-14%"]

    TRUE --- MT --- LT --- MIXED --- LF --- MF --- FALSE

    style TRUE fill:#2e7d32,color:#fff
    style MT fill:#43a047,color:#fff
    style LT fill:#66bb6a,color:#000
    style MIXED fill:#fdd835,color:#000
    style LF fill:#ff9800,color:#000
    style MF fill:#e65100,color:#fff
    style FALSE fill:#b71c1c,color:#fff
{{/mermaid}}

Each verdict includes: truth percentage, confidence tier (High / Medium / Low / Insufficient evidence), supporting and opposing evidence citations, and a full reasoning narrative.

----

== Evidence Quality: Defence in Depth ==

Every piece of evidence passes through **six layers of quality control** before it can influence a verdict. Two phases: pre-verdict evidence quality filtering and post-verdict verdict quality validation.

{{mermaid}}
flowchart LR
    RAW["Raw Evidence\n(LLM extraction)"]:::raw

    subgraph P1["Phase 1: Pre-Verdict Quality"]
        direction LR
        L1["1. Prompt Guidance"]:::phase1
        L2["2. Deterministic Filter\n(length, dedup, category rules)"]:::det
        L3["3. Provenance Validation"]:::det
        L1 --> L2 --> L3
    end

    subgraph P2["Phase 2: Post-Verdict Quality"]
        direction LR
        L4["4. SR Weighting /\nLLM Calibration"]:::det
        L5["5. Aggregation Pruning"]:::det
        L6["6. Validator Checks"]:::det
        L4 --> L5 --> L6
    end

    CLEAN["Published Report\n(verdict + warnings)"]:::clean

    RAW --> L1
    L3 --> L4
    L6 --> CLEAN

    classDef raw fill:#f7e8ea,stroke:#cc8f97,color:#5f2a2f,stroke-width:1.5px
    classDef clean fill:#e8f3e8,stroke:#8cb58f,color:#1f4d2a,stroke-width:1.5px
    classDef phase1 fill:#f8fbff,stroke:#8fb2e5,color:#284f8f,stroke-width:1.2px
    classDef det fill:#fdeaea,stroke:#d08b8b,color:#8a2c2c,stroke-width:1.2px
    style P1 fill:#f4f8ff,stroke:#b7cdef,color:#000,stroke-width:1.2px
    style P2 fill:#fffaf2,stroke:#ecd39b,color:#000,stroke-width:1.2px
    linkStyle default stroke:#666,stroke-width:1.6px
{{/mermaid}}

|=Step|=Type|=What happens
|**1. Prompt Guidance**|LLM-guided|Extraction prompt steers toward source-grounded, specific evidence over vague commentary
|**2. Deterministic Filter**|Deterministic|Structural pass/fail checks: minimum length, probativeValue, URL/excerpt presence, statistic validation
|**3. Provenance Validation**|Deterministic|Evidence must link to a real fetched source with valid URL provenance — synthetic paths rejected
|**4. SR Weighting**|Hybrid|Source Reliability scores per domain (LLM-evaluated) adjust verdict confidence via deterministic weighting formulas
|**5. Aggregation Pruning**|Deterministic|Tangential or low-evidence claims pruned before the final report
|**6. Validator Checks**|Hybrid|Post-verdict grounding and direction checks flag consistency issues

Source reliability scores are computed per-domain using multi-provider LLM evaluation, with cross-check refinement and persistent caching. A peer-reviewed study carries different weight than a social media post — automatically.

----

== Data Model ==

The pipeline produces a richly structured result. Every entity in the output is typed, linked, and inspectable.

{{mermaid}}

erDiagram
    CB_CLAIM_UNDERSTANDING ||--o{ ATOMIC_CLAIM : "contains"
    ATOMIC_CLAIM ||--o{ SEARCH_QUERY : "generates"
    SEARCH_QUERY }o--o{ SOURCE : "retrieves"
    SOURCE ||--o{ EVIDENCE_ITEM : "yields"
    EVIDENCE_ITEM }o--o| EVIDENCE_SCOPE : "may include"
    EVIDENCE_SCOPE }o--|| CLAIM_ASSESSMENT_BOUNDARY : "clusters into"
    EVIDENCE_ITEM }o--o| CLAIM_ASSESSMENT_BOUNDARY : "may be assigned to"
    ATOMIC_CLAIM ||--o| CB_CLAIM_VERDICT : "receives"
    CB_CLAIM_VERDICT }o--o{ EVIDENCE_ITEM : "cites"
    CB_CLAIM_VERDICT }o--|| OVERALL_ASSESSMENT : "aggregates into"
    OVERALL_ASSESSMENT ||--o{ CLAIM_ASSESSMENT_BOUNDARY : "includes"
    OVERALL_ASSESSMENT ||--|| COVERAGE_MATRIX : "includes"
    COVERAGE_MATRIX }o--o{ ATOMIC_CLAIM : "rows"
    COVERAGE_MATRIX }o--o{ CLAIM_ASSESSMENT_BOUNDARY : "columns"
    CB_CLAIM_VERDICT ||--o{ BOUNDARY_FINDING : "contains"
    BOUNDARY_FINDING }o--|| CLAIM_ASSESSMENT_BOUNDARY : "per boundary"

    CB_CLAIM_UNDERSTANDING {
        string detectedInputType "claim question article"
        string impliedClaim "LLM-extracted thesis"
        string backgroundDetails
        string riskTier "A B or C"
    }

    ATOMIC_CLAIM {
        string id_PK "AC_01 AC_02"
        string statement "The verifiable assertion"
        string category "factual evaluative procedural"
        string centrality "high medium"
        string harmPotential "critical high medium low"
        string claimDirection "supports_thesis contradicts_thesis contextual"
        string thesisRelevance "direct tangential irrelevant"
        float specificityScore "0-1 Gate1 min 0.6"
        json keyEntities "Named entities referenced"
    }

    SEARCH_QUERY {
        string query
        int iteration
        string searchProvider
        int resultsCount
    }

    SOURCE {
        string id_PK
        string url
        string title
        float trackRecordScore "0.0-1.0 or null"
        float trackRecordConfidence "0.0-1.0 or null"
        string category
        boolean fetchSuccess
    }

    EVIDENCE_ITEM {
        string id_PK "EV_001 EV_002"
        string statement "Extracted evidence text"
        string sourceId_FK
        string category "statistic expert_quote event etc"
        string claimDirection "supports contradicts neutral"
        string probativeValue "high medium low"
        string sourceType "peer_reviewed_study news_primary etc"
        string sourceAuthority "primary secondary opinion"
        boolean isDerivative "Cites another source study"
    }

    EVIDENCE_SCOPE {
        string name "Short label"
        string methodology "ISO 14040 EU RED II etc"
        string boundaries "Included excluded scope"
        string temporal "Source data time period"
        string geographic "Source data geography"
        string analyticalDimension "What property is measured"
    }

    CLAIM_ASSESSMENT_BOUNDARY {
        string id_PK "CB_01 CB_02"
        string name "Human-readable label"
        string shortName "Short label"
        string description "What this boundary represents"
        string methodology "Dominant methodology"
        string boundaries "Dominant scope boundaries"
        string temporal "Dominant temporal scope"
        string geographic "Dominant geographic scope"
        float internalCoherence "0-1 consistency"
        int evidenceCount
    }

    CB_CLAIM_VERDICT {
        string id_PK
        string claimId_FK
        float truthPercentage "0-100"
        string verdict "7-point scale label"
        float confidence "0-100"
        string confidenceTier "HIGH MEDIUM LOW INSUFFICIENT"
        string reasoning "LLM-generated explanation"
        boolean isContested
        json supportingEvidenceIds_FK
        json contradictingEvidenceIds_FK
    }

    BOUNDARY_FINDING {
        string boundaryId_FK
        string boundaryName
        float truthPercentage "Per-boundary 0-100"
        float confidence "Per-boundary 0-100"
        string evidenceDirection "supports contradicts mixed neutral"
        int evidenceCount
    }

    COVERAGE_MATRIX {
        json claims "AtomicClaim ids rows"
        json boundaries "Boundary ids columns"
        json counts "evidence counts matrix"
    }

    OVERALL_ASSESSMENT {
        float truthPercentage "0-100 weighted"
        string verdict "7-point scale label"
        float confidence "0-100 weighted"
        json verdictNarrative "headline keyFinding limitations"
        boolean hasMultipleBoundaries
        json qualityGates "gate1Stats gate4Stats"
    }

{{/mermaid}}

The original ER diagram above stays authoritative. The styled copy below only emphasizes the core analytical entities visually.

{{mermaid}}
flowchart TB
    UNDER["CB Claim Understanding"]
    AC["Atomic Claim"]
    SQ["Search Query"]
    SRC["Source"]
    EI["Evidence Item"]
    ES["Evidence Scope"]
    CAB["Claim Assessment Boundary"]
    CV["CB Claim Verdict"]
    BF["Boundary Finding"]
